Project dstate (C:/dev/dstate): an agent-owned, self-evolving DAG+FSM state library, now BUILDLESS JAVASCRIPT (ES modules, no types, no tsc) on Bun, persisting via a synchronous libsql client (libsql@0.5.x native addon) behind a db.js facade that re-exposes the bun:sqlite-shaped query(sql).get/all + run(sql,...args) surface, strips libsql's injected _metadata row key, and normalizes binds. Event-sourced spine = append-only hash-chained log (WAL); nodes/edges/zones/stats/cursor are a deterministic projection. One graph is memory (node payloads) + policy (sandboxed guard DSL + soft/hard enforcement + safe transition zones) + intuition (edge stats -> UCB suggest). Public surface = DState facade in src/index.js, plus DState.describe()/manifest.js machine-readable manifest and a `dstate` CLI with --json. Edge lookups use composite (src,kind)/(dst,kind) indexes (libsql's planner otherwise scans on the low-cardinality kind index). Verify: `bun test` (66 unit), `bun test.js` (22-assertion integration witness), `bun run bench` (per-step flat, <10ms budget). xstate intentionally NOT used (would reintroduce eval-class JS guards); floosie skipped (stream/ACP transport, not a state store). No git remote configured -> push is blockedBy external.